\title{Memoryless property}
\taxon{Theorem}

\p{
  If #{ Z \sim \text{Exp}(\lambda )}, then
  ##{
    \mathbb{P} \left( Z >{t+s} | Z >{t}  \right) = \mathbb{P} \left( Z > s \right) \quad \forall s,t \geq 0
  }
}

\p{
  Conversely, the e[xponential distributions](SP-000L) are the only positive random variables enjoying the loss of memory property
}